The '''Kamikura Shrine''' (神倉神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located in {{ill|Shingū, Wakayama|ja|新宮市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shingū, Wakayama|qq=}}, Japan. It is a subordinate shrine of the {{ill|Kumano Hayatama Taisha|ja|熊野速玉大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Hayatama Taisha|qq=}}, part of the {{ill|Kumano shrine|lt=Kumano shrine|lt=Kumano Sanzan|ja|熊野三山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Sanzan|qq=}} complex. The shrine is designated as a National Historic Site under the {{ill|Kumano shrine|lt=Kumano shrine|lt=Kumano Sanzan|ja|熊野三山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Sanzan|qq=}} and is included in the UNESCO World Heritage Site {{ill|Sacred Sites and Pilgrimage Routes in the Kii Mountain Range|ja|紀伊山地の霊場と参詣道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sacred Sites and Pilgrimage Routes in the Kii Mountain Range|qq=}}.

